    {
      "id": "PopularPost337478",
      "post_content": "The Top Comment of this card reflects what WoTC would say to me if they read the Following:   \n  \nThe Top Comment and WoTC are WRONG  \n  \n  \nSince this was revealed, I have reconsidered whether Char is a worthy card at all.   \n  \nChar is a great example of the \"[Lightning Bolt](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning Bolt) is kind of Bad for MAGIC' argument. Bolt DOES somewhat give you a [Tunnel Vision](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tunnel Vision) with regards to judging red cards, thinking purely of 'points of damage for mana', and not enough of 'utility/versatility'. Char is not directly more useful, But, it is Different in a way that allows lots of Designs for cards that are 'more Useful but Weaker' than Bolt. Like how the Ravnica Shocklands are more compelling mechanically, visually, and flavorfully than the Beta Duals. \"Worse Card, but it's for a Good Cause.\"  \n  \nChar's similarity to [Chandra's Outrage](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Chandra's Outrage) can make it seem especially disappointing to see at Mythic Rare in Foil. Since thinking more about Char, I've decided it actually... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "ParallaxtheRevan",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost337478\">\n<span id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_post\">The Top Comment of this card reflects what WoTC would say to me if they read the Following: <br/><br/>The Top Comment and WoTC are WRONG<br/><br/><br/>Since this was revealed, I have reconsidered whether Char is a worthy card at all. <br/><br/>Char is a great example of the \"<a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning Bolt\">Lightning Bolt</a> is kind of Bad for MAGIC' argument. Bolt DOES somewhat give you a <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tunnel Vision\">Tunnel Vision</a> with regards to judging red cards, thinking purely of 'points of damage for mana', and not enough of 'utility/versatility'. Char is not directly more useful, But, it is Different in a way that allows lots of Designs for cards that are 'more Useful but Weaker' than Bolt. Like how the Ravnica Shocklands are more compelling mechanically, visually, and flavorfully than the Beta Duals. \"Worse Card, but it's for a Good Cause.\"<br/><br/>Char's similarity to <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Chandra's Outrage\">Chandra's Outrage</a> can make it seem especially disappointing to see at Mythic Rare in Foil. Since thinking more about Char, I've decided it actually... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 337478)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_reportAbuseLink\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                         